**Overall Meaning:**

"Drawing in the air with the tongue, one should restrain it at the root of the tongue. Drinking this nectar without disturbance, one would attain all happiness."

**Note:** This verse emphasizes the practice of consciously inhaling air with the tongue and holding it at the base of the tongue, aiming to experience a state of calm and bliss. The "nectar" mentioned here symbolizes the inner joy and peace that can be achieved through breath control. 
